codex
The amended decision rule mostly matches the design, but the schema lint fails to enforce one newly introduced frozen preregistration field. That leaves a load-bearing part of the endpoint mutable without test failure.

Review comment:

- [P2] Include the trend-test in frozen-field lint — /home/coreyt/projects/fathomdb/src/python/eval/m1_decision_rule.py:157-163
  Because the amended design adds `frozen-field: trend-test` as the only place that freezes how `trend.neg_significant` is computed, leaving it out of `REQUIRED_FROZEN_FIELDS` means `lint_preregistration()` will still pass if that section is deleted or undated. In that scenario Slice 20 would still have a frozen boolean gate in code but no machine-checked preregistration for the bootstrap slope test that feeds it, undermining the stated “Each frozen-field line below is required” guarantee.
